Find the remainder when $$33818^2 + 33819^2 + 33820^2 + 33821^2 + 33822^2$$is divided by 17.

$$33818^2 + 33819^2 + 33820^2 + 33821^2 + 33822^2$$
$$= (33818 + 33819 + 33820 + 33821 + 33822)^2 - 2(33818 \times 33819 + 33819 \times 33820 + 33820 \times 33821 + 33821 \times 33822)$$
$$= (169100)^2 - 2(33818 \times 33819 + 33819 \times 33820 + 33820 \times 33821 + 33821 \times 33822)$$
$$= 169100^2 - 2(114011402 + 114035220 + 114059038 + 114082856)$$
$$= 169100^2 - 2(456186216)$$
$$= 169100^2 - 912372432$$
$$= 778627568$$
$$= 778627568 \equiv 1 \pmod{17}$$
Final Answer: \boxed{1}. I hope it is correct.
